episodes.name: Christmas Special | Ep 11

episodes.name: Devil May Cry 4, Turok, & The State Of The Aussie Games Industry | Ep 1
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review Devil May Cry 4 and Turok, plus we investigate the state of the Aussie games industry.

episodes.name: Lost Oddysey, Burnout Paradise, Zack & Wiki, & Online Relationships | Ep 2
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo bring you reviews of the epic RPG Lost Oddysey, the smash happy open world racing of Burnout Paradise, and the Wii pirate puzzling of Zack & Wiki! Plus, Bajo looks back into the work of Final Fantasy creator Hironobu Sakaguchi, and Lux investigates the world of online romance!

episodes.name: Audiosurf, Pac-Man CE, Patapon, & The History Of Online Gaming | Ep 3
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist round up a whole heap of downloadable games for review, there’s the reinvented arcade action of Pac-Man CE, the use your own music rhythm of Audiosurf, the pew pew shoot em ups Everyday Shooter and Omega 5, and the strategy game that marches to its own beat in Patapon. Plus, Jung looks back at the history of online gaming!

episodes.name: Bajo Goes To GDC, DOW: Soulstorm, & The History Of The Dreamcast! | Ep 4
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the pirate MMO Pirates Of The Burning Sea, & the expansion to the Warhammer RTS Dawn Of War: Soulstorm. Plus, Bajo heads off to San Francisco to check out the Game Developers Conference, and still has time to tell the history of the beloved but doomed Sega Dreamcast.

episodes.name: Army Of Two, Advance Wars: Days Of Ruin, & An Interview With Will Wright! | Ep 5
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist bring you reviews of the handheld strategy gem Advance Wars: Days of Ruin, and the co-op cover shooting action of Army of Two. Plus, some big name devs share their tips on how to start designing a good game! Plus, Bajo sits down and has a long chat with a legend of the industry, the creator of Sim City, Will Wright!

episodes.name: Frontline: Fuel Of War, Lost: Via Domus, And Can Games Get You Fit? | Ep 6
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the online focused FPS Frontline: Fuel Of War, and the awful video game tie in Lost: Via Domus. Plus, they investigate whether games can help get you fit, Jung visits the Game On exhibition at ACMI, and looks into the history of health bars in games.

episodes.name: God Of War: Chains Of Olympus, Rainbow Six: Vegas 2, And The Game The Army Uses! | Ep 7
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review the the handheld PSP outing for Kratos, God Of War: Chains Of Olympus, and Ubisoft’s high rolling tactical shooter Rainbow Six: Vegas 2. Plus, Bajo visits Bohemia Interactive Australia to look at the game the Army uses to train, Jung dives into the history of QTE’s, and Lux looks at the skill shortage in the Australian games industry.

episodes.name: No More Heroes, Pipe Buster, Turning Point: FoL & Why Games Cost So Much In Australia? | Ep 8
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the oddball stylish action of No More Heroes, journey to brown town in Pipe Buster, and the alternate reality WW2 FPS Turning Point: Fall Of Liberty. Plus, Junglist investigates why games cost so much in Australia, and Bajo delivers a guide on gaming lingo.

episodes.name: Professor Layton & The Curious Village, GT5: Prologue, & Sins Of A Solar Empire! | Ep 9
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review the handheld puzzling of Professor Layton And The Curious Village, the tantalizing taste of racing in Gran Turismo 5: Prologue, and the four X space strategy of Sins Of A Solar Empire. Plus, Jung dives into the history of puzzle games!

episodes.name: C&C 3: Kane’s Wrath, Best Free Games, Peter Molyneux Interview, & Violence In Games! | Ep 10
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the RTS expansion Command & Conquer 3: Kane’s Wrath, dive into a batch of good free games like Trackmania, Warsaw and Runescape. Plus, we sit down for an in depth chat with Peter Molyneux, and Lux looks into the controversial discussion of how and if violent games affect violence in players.

episodes.name: Mario Kart Wii, Castlevania PSP, Ikaruga, And The History Of Video Game Ninjas! | Ep 11
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review the kart racing classic Mario Kart Wii, the castle crawling action on the go of Castlevania for PSP, and the colour-shifting bullet hell punishment of Ikaruga! Plus Junglist dives into the history of Ninjas in video games, and some GG fans get the behind the scenes treatment in the Good Game Open Day!

episodes.name: Time Crisis 4, Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn, Rockband, & The History Of Rockstar North! | Ep 12
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the arcade to console port of Time Crisis 4, the Wii port of Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn, and the party rhythm action of Rockband. Plus, Junglist dives into the history of Rockstar North!

episodes.name: Grand Theft Auto IV, UEFA Euro 2008, Young Gamers, & The History Of The Atari Lynx! | Ep 13
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review the epic action of Grand Theft Auto IV, and the ball kicking of UEFA Euro 2008. Plus, Investigator Bajo investigates how gaming affects younger gamers, and looks into the history of the Atari Lynx!

episodes.name: Wii Fit, Iron Man, Games In Sports, & The History Of Power-Ups! | Ep 14
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the mediocre movie tie in of Iron Man, and the game that wants to get you fit, Wii Fit. Plus, Junglist investigates the role games are playing in professional sports training, and looks into the history of power-ups!

episodes.name: Boom Blox, The World Ends With You, Aussie Esports, & The History Of The Power Glove! | Ep 15
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review the unique and trendy RPG of The World Ends With You, and the Steven Spielberg produced block destroying of Boom Blox. Plus, Junglist investigates the state of Aussie Esports, and Bajo dives into the history of the Power Glove!

episodes.name: Haze, Racedriver: GRID, Game Piracy, & Can Games Get You Better? | Ep 16
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the much hyped but not so good Haze, and the intense racing of Racedriver: GRID. Plus, Bajo investigates the effect of games piracy on the industry, and Jung and Lux take a look at how games help kids in hospital.

episodes.name: Soul Calibur IV, Guitar Hero: Aerosmith, & The E3 2008 Report! | Ep 17
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review the stylish weapon slinging slugfest of Soul Calibur IV, and the rhythm spin off of Guitar Hero: Aerosmith. Plus, Bajo brings you his report from E3 2008!

episodes.name: Braid, Beijing 2008, The History Of Olympics Video Games, & Peter Moore Interview | Ep 18
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the brain bending beauty of Braid, and the boring button mashing of Beijing 2008. Plus, Junglist dives into the less than gold-medal worthy history of games based on the Olympics, checks out the World Cyber Games qualifies, and we chat to industry veteran Peter Moore!

episodes.name: Space Siege, Too Human, & The History Of The Longest In-Development Games! Ep 19
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review the isometric blasting of Space Siege, and the sci-fi meets Norse mythology action of Too Human. Plus, we follow our Good Game Game winners on their first day at work, interview a bunch of big developers on their Zombie games, and take a look at the history of the games that languished the longest in development hell.

episodes.name: Mercenaries 2, Trauma Centre: Second Opinion, & The History Of Will Wright’s Games | Ep 20
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the medical drama of Trauma Centre: Second Opinion, and the open world destruction fest of Mercenaries 2. Plus, Lux looks into why it is us humans love to play games, and Bajo dives into the work of industry icon Will Wright.

episodes.name: Spore, Viva Pinata: Trouble In Paradise, & The History Of Star Wars Games | Ep 21
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review the ambitious sim of everything, Spore, and the cute gardening slash piñata collecting on Viva Pinata: Trouble In Paradise. Plus, Junglist dives into the history of Star Wars video games.

episodes.name: Star Wars: The Force Unleashed, Machinima, & The History Of Game & Watch | Ep 22
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the epic JRPG Infinite Undiscovery, and the lightsaber swinging and force pushing of Star Wars: The Force Unleashed. Plus, Bajo attempts to make some Machinima in GTA IV and sits down to chat to some pros like Red vs Blue’s Bernie Burns to get some tips, and dives into the history of Nintendo’s Game and Watch series.

episodes.name: Wario Land: TSD, Warhammer: AoR, & The History Of Aussie Games | Ep 23
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review the tabletop come MMO of Warhammer: Age Of Reckoning, and the platforming puzzles of Wario Land : The Shake Dimension. Plus, Bajo sits down with one of the creator of de Blob, Junglist looks into how game artists got their start in the industry, and Bajo and Jung dive into the history of games made in Australia and by Australians.

episodes.name: FIFA 09, de Blob, Pure, the History Of Soccer Games, & Double The Fist Roffle Cup | Ep 24
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the much hyped but not so good Haze, and the intense racing of Racedriver: GRID. Plus, Bajo investigates the effect of games piracy on the industry, and Jung and Lux take a look at how games help kids in hospital.

episodes.name: GG Shocks the 80’s! ET: The Extra Terrestrial, Super Mario Bros, Gaming In The 80’s | Ep 25
episodes.overview: In this special throwback episode Bajo and Junglist hit up the 80’s! They review the best and the worst of the decade with ET: The Extra Terrestrial and Super Mario Bros reviews. Plus, they dive into the history of the decade, and have a Roffle cup with Andrew “Bindi” Hansen!

episodes.name: Saints Row 2, Fracture, & The History Of Sandbox Games | Ep 26
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the contender to the sandbox game throne, Saints Row 2, and the deforming destruction of Fracture. Plus, Bajo and Junglist dive into the history of sandbox games, and we get an update on the Good Game Game.

episodes.name: LittleBigPlanet, Fable 2, & How To Get A Job As A Programmer | Ep 27
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review the creative and colourful platformer LittleBigPlanet, and the choose your morality fantasy role playing of Fable 2. Plus, Jung looks into how to get started as a game programmer, and joins Bajo to list out some of the hardest games they’ve ever played, while Bajo heads out to visit a man with a very serious game collection.

episodes.name: Dead Space, Far Cry 2, PES 2009, & The History Of Epic Games | Ep 28
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the sci-fi horror of Dead Space, the ambitious open world first person shooting of Far Cry 2, and a mini Pro Evolution Soccer 2009 review. Plus, Bajo dives into the history of Epic Games, and visits the offices of Infinite interactive to see how the Good Game Game is shaping up!

episodes.name: Midnight Club: LA, Fallout 3, Gears Of War 2, & Moral Challenges In Games | Ep 29
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review some huge games, with Rockstars take on racers in Midnight Club: LA, the post-apocalyptic RPG epic Fallout 3, and make probably the most unique review of Gears Of War 2 in the world. Plus, Junglist investigates how games can help test our moral compass, and plays a round of FIFA with Craig Foster in a Roffle Cup.

episodes.name: Guitar Hero World Tour, Rock Band, EndWar, Mirror’s Edge, & Why People Cheat | Ep 30
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the voice controlled RTS of Tom Clancy’s End War, the bright parkour fueled dystopia of Mirror’s Edge, and they take Guitar Hero World Tour and Rock Band head to head to see which rhythm game comes out on top. Plus, Lux investigates the psychology of why people like to cheat in games.

episodes.name: Quantum Of Solace, Resistance 2, C&C Red Alert 3, COD: World At War| Ep 31
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review a heap of games, including the James Bond movie game Quantum Of Solace, the WW2 meets alien invasion FPS Resistance 2, the alternate history RTS of Command and Conquer: Red Alert 3, the gritty WW2 FPS Call of Duty: World at War, and the zany party game Rayman Raving Rabbids TV Party. Plus, the Good Game Game gets launched!

episodes.name: NFS Undercover, MK vs DCU, Banjo-Kazooie Nuts n’ Bolts, Left 4 Dead, Wii Music | Ep 32
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo try to cram as many reviews in as they can in the final episode of the season. With reviews of Need For Speed Undercover, Singstar Singalong With Disney, Mortal Kombat vs DC Universe, Banjo Kazooie Nuts n’ Bolts, Wii Music, LIPS, and Left 4 Dead. Plus, Bajo sits down and chats with Michael Atkinson about his stance against the introduction of an R18+ rating in Australia.

episodes.name: Skate 2, Lord of the Rings Conquest, Interpol & Street Fighter IV Challenge
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist return from their holidays to get back into a big year of gaming. Kicking things off with reviews of Skate 2, Lord of the Rings Conquest and Interpol: The Trail of Dr. Chaos!

episodes.name: F.E.A.R. 2: Project Origin, Killzone 2 & Warhammer 40,000: Dawn of War II
episodes.overview: This episode saw some massive releases up for review with FPS titans Killzone 2 and F.E.A.R 2: Project Origin, and the follow up to an excellent RTS classic with Warhammer 40,000: Dawn of War II. Plus, Junglist gives us a backward compatible run down through the history of Warhammer games.

episodes.name: Halo Wars, Street Fighter IV & Fire Emblem: Shadow Dragon
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review Halo Wars, Fire Emblem: Shadow Dragon, and Street Fighter IV. Plus, we meet our new field reporter Rei who checks out some art inspired by games. And we go Backward Compatible to look at the history of one of the greatest consoles of all time, the SNES!

episodes.name: GTA IV: The Lost and Damned, Flower & Puzzle Quest: Galactrix
episodes.overview: In this episode Junglist and Bajo review GTA IV: The Lost and Damned, Flower, and Puzzle Quest: Galactrix. Plus, Bajo investigates how to conserve our delicate gaming equipment, and we go Backward Compatible with the history of companions in games.

episodes.name: Empire: Total War, Tom Clancy’s H.A.W.X. & Overclockers
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review the high flying action of H.A.W.X and the historical strategy of Empire: Total War. Plus, Bajo talks about Sonic for a bit, and Rei checks out a local Overclocking competition!

episodes.name: The Zombie Special! Feat. Resident Evil 5 & Silent Hill: Homecoming
episodes.overview: In this flesh-eating feast Bajo and Junglist get their teeth into reviews of Dead Rising: Chop Till You Drop, House of the Dead: Overkill, Resident Evil 5 and Silent Hill: Homecoming. Plus, we go Backward Compatible to take a look at the history of Zombie games!

episodes.name: Patapon 2, Codename: Panzers – Cold War & Watchmen: The End Is Nigh
episodes.overview: This week Bajo and Junglist slap some scores on Patapon 2, Watchmen: The End Is Night & Codename: Panzers – Cold War. Plus, we go behind the scenes at Creative Assembly to check out their console RTS Stormrise.

episodes.name: GTA: China Town Wars, Football Manager Live, Stormrise & Resistance: Retribution
episodes.overview: It’s a game packed week with reviews of Grand Theft Auto: China Town Wars, Football Manager Live, Stormrise & Resistance Retribution. Plus, Rei investigates how to keep gaming when the going gets tough.

episodes.name: The Godfather 2, Wallace & Gromit, Wanted & MadWorld
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo bring you reviews of The Godfather 2, Wallace & Gromit: Fright of the Bumblebees, Wanted: Weapons of Fate & MadWorld. Plus, we check out the local chiptunes scene with artists Dot.AY and 10k!

episodes.name: And Yet It Moves, Wheelman & The History Of Easter Eggs
episodes.overview: This week the dynamic duo reviews the puzzles of And Yet It Moves and the Vin Diesel driven Wheelman. Plus, Bajo talks about Easter eggs in games as an excuse to eat some chocolate, and Junglist discusses what it means to be a casual or hardcore gamer.

episodes.name: Afro Samurai, Dishwasher: Dead Samurai & FIFA 09: Ultimate Team
episodes.overview: Samurai! And Soccer! A classic combo as shown by this week’s reviews of Afro Samurai, Dishwasher: Dead Samurai and FIFA 09: Ultimate Team. Plus, we check out how to get a career in game design and dive into the history of the Gameboy!

episodes.name: The Chronicles of Riddick: Assault on Dark Athena & Flock
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review The Chronicles Of Riddick: Assault on Dark Athena and Flock. Plus, Rei investigates how an internet filter would work, and we go Backwards Compatible on the history of heroines in games.

episodes.name: X-Men Origins: Wolverine & Leisure Suit Larry: Box Office Bust
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist get their claws into their review of X-Men Origins Wolverine, and also check out Leisure Suit Larry: Box Office Bust. Plus, Bajo discusses the rise of DLC and we go Backwards Compatible on the history of controversial games.

episodes.name: Quake Live, Little King’s Story, The Chronicles of Spellborn & The Runes of Magic
episodes.overview: This episode there’s reviews of Quake Live, Little King’s Story, The Chronicles of Spellborn & The Runes of Magic. Plus, Bajo looks at how games can be used to educate, and Junglist goes Backward Compatible on the history of Edutainment.

episodes.name: Demigod, Virtua Tennis 2009 & OutRun Online Arcade
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review Demigod, Virtua Tennis 2009 and OutRun Online Arcade. Plus, Rei investigates the state of women working in the games industry and Junglist and Bajo revisit some older games to see how time has treated them.

episodes.name: Plants vs Zombies, Killing Floor, UFC 2009 & Guitar Hero: Metallica
episodes.overview: Junglist and Bajo review two very different type of zombie games with Plants vs Zombies and Killing Floor, plus reviews of UFC 2009: Undisputed and Guitar Hero Metallica. We also go Backward Compatible with the history of 3D Realms, and Lawrence Leung takes us on a Game and Watch Adventure.

episodes.name: inFAMOUS, Terminator: Salvation & Damnation
episodes.overview: This episode we review the super powered open world of InFamous, and also check out Terminator Salvation & Damnation. Plus, Rei checks out the 2009 Pinball Expo and Junglist goes Backward Compatible into the history of The Virtual Boy.

episodes.name: The 90’s Special: Feat: Quake & The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time
episodes.overview: It’s a 90’s nostalgia fest! With reviews of the seminal FPS Quake, and the beloved classic The Legend Of Zelda: Ocarina of Time. Plus, Rei investigates the influence the 90’s had on our culture and we go Backward Compatible on the entire gaming history of the 90’s.

episodes.name: The 2009 E3 Report, The Sims 3 & Red Faction: Guerrilla
episodes.overview: We put up some walls and tear them right back down in reviews of The Sims 3 and Red Faction: Guerrilla. Plus, Junglist brings us his report from the 2009 E3 show floor!

episodes.name: Ghostbusters: The Video Game & Bionic Commando
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist try not to cross the streams in their review of Ghostbusters: The Video Game, and the 3D imagining of Bionic Commando. Plus, Rei investigates the history of Flash and Browser games, and we go Backwards Compatible on the history of unreleased video games that got leaked!

episodes.name: Prototype, FUEL & Lego Battles
episodes.overview: This episode saw the super anti-hero antics of Prototype get slapped with a score, along with FUEL and Lego Battles. Plus, Junglist takes a look into the art of storytelling…

episodes.name: Blood Bowl & Magic The Gathering: Duels of the Planeswalkers
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review the Warhammer meets football fantasy that is Blood Bowl and the card on card action of Magic the Gathering: Duels of the Planeswalkers. Plus, Rei investigates the world of Cosplay and we go Backwards Compatible with the history of Michael Jackson in video games.

episodes.name: Fight Night Round 4, Call of Juarez: Bound in Blood & Tales Of Monkey Island
episodes.overview: It’s boxing, cowboys and monkeys this episode with reviews of Fight Night Round 4, Call of Juarez: Bound in Bloow, and Tales of Monkey Island: Launch of the Screaming Narwhal. Plus Rei takes a look at the rise of the Blogosphere and Bajo goes backward compatible into the history of pointless cheats.

episodes.name: Inside Valve Software, ARMA II & Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince
episodes.overview: This episode there’s reviews of the wand waving movie tie in Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince and the tough as nails combat simulation of ARMA II. Plus, Junglist gets to go inside Valve studio and spend some time chatting with Gabe Newell!

episodes.name: Battlefield 1943, Battlefield Heroes, Trine, Faerie Solitaire & The Conduit
episodes.overview: This episode Bajo and Junglist take to the battlefields in reviews of Battlefield 1943 and Battlefield Heroes, plus reviews of Trine, Faerie Solitaire & The Conduit. And we go Backward Compatible as we look at the history of classic LucasArts Adventure games.

episodes.name: ‘Splosion Man, Ninja Blade & Madballs in Babo: Invasion
episodes.overview: We got a lot of ‘Splodin to do in our review of ‘Splosion Man, plus reviews of Ninja Blade and Madballs in Babo: Invasion. And Rei takes a look at the world of Art games.

episodes.name: Ashes Cricket 2009, Fat Princess & CSManager
episodes.overview: This episode we review Ashes Cricket 2009, Fat Princess and the Counter Strike Management game CSManager. Plus, Rei takes a look at studying game design and we go Backwards Compatible with the history of the most tasteless games ever made.

episodes.name: Batman: Arkham Asylum, Wolfenstein & Shadow Complex
episodes.overview: It’s an action-packed episode with reviews of Batman: Arkham Asylum, Wolfenstein & Shadow Complex! Plus, Junglist shares his tips on how to justify your gaming to anyone who gives you any sass about it and we answer more questions in Ask Good Game.

episodes.name: Dissidia: Final Fantasy, IL-2 Sturmovik & Spider: The Secret Of Bryce Manor
episodes.overview: This episode Bajo and Junglist review Dissidia: Final Fantasy, IL-2 Sturmovik: Birds of Prey, & Spider: The Secret Of Bryce Manor. Plus, Rei investigates how respectable gaming has become as a hobby and Bajo goes Backward Compatible into the history of food in games.

episodes.name: Soul Calibur: Broken Destiny, Supercar Challenge & Champions Online
episodes.overview: We get our super hero pants on in a review of the MMO Champions Online, plus reviews of Soul Calibur: Broken Destiny and Supercar Challenge. Bajo and Junglist also work up a sweat to find out if games can get us fit.

episodes.name: Halo 3: ODST, Guitar Hero 5, The Beatles: Rock Band & A Chat With The Voice Of Mario
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist drop down to Earth to review the Halo spin-off Halo 3: ODST, plus the plastic smacking juggernauts Guitar Hero 5 and The Beatles: Rock Band get smacked with some rubber chickens, as does some Mini Ninjas. Plus, we chat to Charles Martinet, the voice of all things Mario!

episodes.name: NFS: Shift, Dirt 2, Scribblenauts & Marvel Ultimate Alliance 2
episodes.overview: We burn some rubber in our reviews of Need For Speed: Shift and Dirt 2, plus reviews of Scribblenauts & Marvel Ultimate Alliance 2. Plus we visit Jono Pearson, Australia’s fastest Tetris player!

episodes.name: Aion & Professor Leyton and Pandora’s Box
episodes.overview: Bajo and Junglist review the ambitious MMO Aion and Professor Leyton and Pandora’s Box. And speaking of Pandora, they check out an early version of Borderlands. Plus, Rei checks out the Eminence Orchestra and the importance of music in games and we dive into the history of boss battles.

episodes.name: Uncharted 2: Among Thieves, FIFA 10 & Operation Flashpoint: Dragon Rising
episodes.overview: This episode we check out one of the best action games of all time, Uncharted 2: Among Thieves, plus FIFA 10 and Operation Flashpoint Dragon Rising. Plus, Gabe Newell came to town and we followed him and a persistent modder who demanded Gabe check out his mod!

episodes.name: Brutal Legend, Gran Turismo (PSP), Lucidity & Beaterator
episodes.overview: Things get a bit metal this episode in our review of Brutal Legend, and we check out Gran Turismo for PSP, Lucidity and Beaterator. Plus, we go Backward Compatible on the history of stealth games, and visit another of Australia’s best gamers, Rodney Day, the man who holds the record for holding a record the longest!

episodes.name: Forza Motorsport 3 & Kingdom Hearts 358/2 Days
episodes.overview: In this episode we welcome Hex to the show and throw her in the deep end with reviews of Forza Motorsport 3 and Kingdom Hearts 358/2 Days. Plus, Rei investigates the 400 Project from game designer Noah Falstein, laying down the 400 rules of game design.

episodes.name: Borderlands, GTA IV: The Ballad of Gay Tony, Cities XL & G-Force
episodes.overview: Bajo and Hex head to the Bordlerlands to review… Borderlands, plus reviews of GTA IV: The Ballad of Gay Tony, Cities XL & G-Force. We also have a cheeky round of golf with Matthew Reilly in a Roffle Cup, and dive into the history of Simulator games.

episodes.name: Tekken 6, DJ Hero & Dragon Age: Origins Interview
episodes.overview: Hex and Bajo fight it out in their review of Tekken 6, and spin some records in DJ Hero. Plus, they interview Dr. Greg Zeschuck from BioWare about Dragon Age: Origins, and Rei investigates Virtual Simulator Sickness, the unfortunate case of people getting motion sick playing games.

episodes.name: COD: MW2, Dragon Age: Origins, New Super Mario Bros. Wii & Ratchet & Clank: A Crack in Time
episodes.overview: What a huge week for games with blockbusters Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2 and Dragon Age: Origins up for review, along with family friendly classics New Super Mario Bros. Wii and Ratchet & Clank: A Crack In Time. Plus, Rei takes a look at the rise of digital distribution and how it’s changing our gaming habits.

episodes.name: Assassin’s Creed 2, LittleBigPlanet (PSP) & Singing Game Round-Up
episodes.overview: We review the follow to one of Hex’s favourite games, Assassin’s Creed 2, and look at Sackboy’s portable outing in LittleBigPlanet for PSP, plus round up a whole bunch of singing games like Singstar Motown, Singstar Take That, and U-Sing. Plus, we go Backwards Compatible with games that let us be bad and meet another of Australia’s best gamers, Phil Day, the world Galaga champ!

episodes.name: The Christmas Special! Feat: Left 4 Dead 2 & The Legend of Zelda: Spirit Tracks
episodes.overview: It’s the end of the year which means it’s time for a Christmas special! Along with handing out our yearly best of awards we find time to review a heap of games, including Left 4 Dead 2, Lego Rock Band, Band Hero, James Cameron’s Avatar: The Game, The Saboteur, Rush Rush Rally Racing, Lego Indiana Jones 2: The Adventure Continues & The Legend of Zelda: Spirit Tracks. Phew, that’s a lot of games! Plus, Rei investigates how gaming can be the greatest gift to those in need, and we take a look back through the past decade of gaming!

episodes.name: Mass Effect 2, BioShock 2 & The R18+ Debate
episodes.overview: Bajo and Hex return for the year with two huge reviews, going into deep space with Mass Effect 2, and into the depths of the ocean in BioShock 2. Plus, we continue to investigate the progress of getting an R18+ classification category for video games!

episodes.name: Heavy Rain, Dante’s Inferno, The WASD System & Game Jams
episodes.overview: It’s the episode with more brown pants and Jason’s than you can mash X at as we review David Cage’s thriller, Heavy Rain, plus we venture into the depths of hell in Dante’s Inferno. Plus, we look into the story of how we ended up with the WASD keyboard, and visit a game jam to watch some devs cram a game together in 48 hours!

episodes.name: Aliens vs Predator, M.A.G. & The History Of Final Fantasy
episodes.overview: Bajo and Hex review the interspecies action of Aliens vs Predator, and the massive action of M.A.G. aka Massive Action Game. Plus. We take a deep two-part backward compatible dive into the history of the Final Fantasy series, and visit game collector Matt Goodwin!

episodes.name: Battlefield: Bad Company 2, Final Fantasy XIII & P.B. Winterbottom
episodes.overview: This episode we blow stuff up in our review of one of our all-time favourite FPS’s, Battlefield: Bad Company 2. Plus, we go on an epic adventure in Final Fantasy XIII, and a time-bending misadventure in The Misadventures of P.B. Winterbottom. And we go Backward Compatible on the career of the biggest Llama fan in gaming, Jeff Minter.

episodes.name: Metro 2033, God Of War III & The History Of The Elder Scrolls
episodes.overview: We venture into the dark post-apocalyptic subways of Metro 2033, and take down a god or two in God Of War III. Plus, we go Backward Compatible on the history of the Elder Scrolls series, and Hex rounds up five of the best weapons in gaming.

episodes.name: C&C 4: Tiberian Twilight, Napoleon: Total War & Supreme Commander 2
episodes.overview: This week it’s all strategy, all the time with reviews of Command & Conquer 4: Tiberian Twilight, Napoleon: Total War & Supreme Commander 2. Plus, we get an experts opinion on the StarCraft 2 beta, and round up five of the best strategies to use in RTS games.

episodes.name: Just Cause 2, Red Steel 2 & We Meet Ajax
episodes.overview: It’s another explosive episode as we grapple our way through the destruction of Just Cause 2, and take on some sword swinging shenanigans in Red Steel 2. Plus, we meet our new field reported Ajax.

episodes.name: Perfect Dark, Dragon Age: Origins – Awakening, Pipe Buster: Number Twos
episodes.overview: This episode we review the XBLA re-release of the N64 classic, Perfect Dark, and get stuck into the first big expansion for Dragon Age: Origins, Awakening, look at the follow up to everyone’s favourite poop management simulator Pipe Buster: Number Twos, and round up a bunch of mobile games, Space Miner, Ragdoll Blaster 2, and Crash Nitro Kart 3D. And Ajax investigates a man who’s built a fully functional flight simulator in his own home!

episodes.name: BlazBlue: Calamity Trigger, Rugby League 3 & Games vs Sleep
episodes.overview: Hex and Bajo review the popular fighter BlazBlue: Calamatiy Trigger and try to sport in Rugby League 3. Plus, Ajax investigates the effect our late night gaming sessions are having on our health, and Bajo rounds up five of the funniest moments in games.

episodes.name: Splinter Cell: Conviction & The Settlers 7: Paths to a Kingdom
episodes.overview: We review the stylish sneaky action of Splinter Cell: Conviction, and settle in for  some strategy in The Settlers 7: Paths to a Kingdom. Plus, we visit the FIFA Interactive World Cup Qualifiers and look into the ever growing business of game remakes.

episodes.name: Monster Hunter Tri, Torchlight & Gaming Moustaches
episodes.overview: This episode we review the monster slaying action of Monster Hunter Tri, and the top down loot em ups of Torchlight. Plus, Bajo lists the top five moustaches in gaming, and we visit a man who keeps old consoles ticking.

episodes.name: What Impact Do Violent Games Have On Us?
episodes.overview: This episode sees our field reporter, Ajax, investigate the long running discussion on what, if any, effect violent video games have on their players. Plus, we review Dead To Rights: Retribution, and The Sky Crawlers: Innocent Aces, while Hex lists the top five worst bits of voice acting in games.

episodes.name: ModNation Racers, 2010 FIFA World Cup South Africa, & M.U.D. TV
episodes.overview: It’s a review packed episode with reviews of the creative kart racing in ModNation Racers, the ball kicking of 2010 FIFA World Cup South Africa, the TV making of M.U.D. TV, and the lead slinging of Lead and Gold: Gangs of the Wild West. Plus, we meet the national Guitar Hero Champion, Joel Brooks.

episodes.name: Alan Wake & Super Street Fighter IV
episodes.overview: This episode we look at the ambitious psychological thriller from the minds behind Max Payne, Alan Wake, and we chuck some hadoukens and rubber chickens at Super Street Fighter IV. Plus, Ajax investigates how to protect your precious gaming gear from would be thieves!

episodes.name: Prince of Persia: The Forgotten Sands & 3D Dot Game Heroes
episodes.overview: This episode has more games crammed in it than you can shake a rainbow unicorn at! There are reviews of the pixel block adventures of 3D Dot Game Heroes, the time bending climbing of Prince of Persia: The Forgotten Sands, the hit unicorn leaping of Robot Unicorn Attack, the 4X action of Neptune’s Pride, and the fly boy antics of After Burner Climax! Plus, Ajax gives his tips for how to dominate in the gaming Lounge Room!

episodes.name: Red Dead Redemption & Lost Planet 2
episodes.overview: We saddle up to review one of the biggest and best games ever made, Red Dead Redemption. Plus, we blow up some aliens in the cold in Lost Planet 2. And we take a look at the history of Sensible Software.

episodes.name: Skate 3, Alpha Protocol & UFC Undisputed 2010
episodes.overview: We get kick-flip and ollie our way through our review of the excellent Skate 3, make some tough choices in the spy driven espionage world of Alpha Protocol, and step into the octagon for UFC Undisputed 2010. Plus, Bajo ponders over all those games that never get finished and are left in our piles of shame.

episodes.name: Fruit Ninja, Blur & Jolly Roger
episodes.overview: We review the fruit slicing and dicing mobile action of Fruit Ninja, the Mario Kart meets Fast and Furios racing of Blur, and the pirate point and click Jolly Roger. Plus, Hex dives into the history of vampires in games.

episodes.name: No More Heroes 2, Toy Story 3 & The History of Rare
episodes.overview: We review the thoroughly bizarre No More Heroes 2: Desperate Struggle, and the much more wholesome Toy Story 3: The Video Game. Plus, we look at the history of one of the most influential studios in gaming history, Rare.

episodes.name: The E3 2010 Special!
episodes.overview: Bajo brings us his special report direct from the biggest event in the gaming calendar, E3 2010!

episodes.name: Super Mario Galaxy 2, Split/Second Velocity & Gaming Addiction
episodes.overview: This week we’ve got reviews of the out of this world platforming utopia of Super Mario Galaxy 2, and the explosive racing of Split/Second Velocity. Plus, Ajax investigates how addictive gaming can be for some.

episodes.name: MGS: Peace Walker, Naughty Bear & Transformers: War for Cybertron
episodes.overview: We review the portable stealth masterpiece Metal Gear Solid: Peace Walker, the absolutely not a masterpiece Naughty Bear, and the surprisingly good Transformers: War for Cybertron, and it’s Wii version Cybertron Adventures. Plus, we meet the minds behind the viral sensation of Beached Az!

episodes.name: We Visit Treyarch’s Studio! Plus, Crackdown 2 & Singularity
episodes.overview: This week on the show, we review Crackdown 2 and Singularity, plus we visit Treayrch's Studio!

episodes.name: Demon’s Souls, Limbo, Joe Danger & DeathSpank
episodes.overview: We review the game that started the whole Souls genre, Demon’s Souls, plus the gloomy platforming masterpiece of Limbo, the stunt bike riding of Joe Danger, and the lighthearted evil adventure of DeathSpank. Also, Bajo names the top five most influential gaming controllers!
